I haven't been able to reproduce, though the following diff should be able to reproduce the out-of-disk crash faster (even with an unlimited disk):

```diff
diff --git a/src/test/util/setup_common.cpp b/src/test/util/setup_common.cpp
index 5334c4623..5d8478632 100644
--- a/src/test/util/setup_common.cpp
+++ b/src/test/util/setup_common.cpp
@@ -90,6 +90,7 @@ BasicTestingSetup::BasicTestingSetup(const std::string& chainName, const std::ve
         },
         extra_args);
     util::ThreadRename("test");
+    Assert(!fs::exists(fs::temp_directory_path() / "test_common_" PACKAGE_NAME));
     fs::create_directories(m_path_root);
     m_args.ForceSetArg("-datadir", m_path_root.string());
     gArgs.ForceSetArg("-datadir", m_path_root.string());

With the "historic afl" (new process each time), I had to adjust the patch for an early crash:

```diff
diff --git a/src/test/util/setup_common.cpp b/src/test/util/setup_common.cpp
index 5334c4623..01e969b49 100644
--- a/src/test/util/setup_common.cpp
+++ b/src/test/util/setup_common.cpp
@@ -90,6 +90,7 @@ BasicTestingSetup::BasicTestingSetup(const std::string& chainName, const std::ve
         },
         extra_args);
     util::ThreadRename("test");
+    Assert(fs::is_empty(fs::temp_directory_path() / "test_common_" PACKAGE_NAME));
     fs::create_directories(m_path_root);
     m_args.ForceSetArg("-datadir", m_path_root.string());
     gArgs.ForceSetArg("-datadir", m_path_root.string());
```

It didn't crash after 12 hours.

